<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-164-216  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 164 216.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Feb 19 1990 n355 p3(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>GSA pushes for pricing details: industry expected to resisteffort. (General Services Administration)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Clancy, Heather.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The General Services Administration is requesting more extensivepricing data from computer hardware and software vendors andresellers during its 1990-1991 schedule year.andP;  The policy hasstirred unrest and uncertainty among channel representatives whowill be forced to ask vendors for proprietary informationconcerning discounts for OEM sales, educational promotions andother matters.andP;  The move by the GSA is based on the concern thatit is not receiving the best prices on certain products,particularly in the software arena.andP;  The Software Publishers Assocresponded to the GSA announcement by sending a letter advising its565 members that compliance was not mandatory under current GSAregulations.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. General Services AdministrationSoftware Publishers AssociationPricing PolicyVendorsComputer IndustryValue-Added ResellersGovernment ContractsSoftware Publishers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>